==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liquidator
<hw>Liq"ui*da`tor</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧k"w⟦icr⟧*d⟦amac⟧`t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>liquidateur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, liquidates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An officer appointed to conduct the winding up of a
company, to bring and defend actions and suits in its name, and to do
all necessary acts on behalf of the company.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>liquidise</ent>⟦br⟧
